{"body":"## Summary\n\nFixes #390.\n\nThis PR restores the GitHub release path after the repository reached a split state where crates.io and git tags advanced to `v0.177.0`, but GitHub Releases stopped at `v0.153.0`.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n- `scripts/create-github-release.rs` treated any GitHub API `Validation Failed` response as an idempotent duplicate release, so the CI/CD run for `0.177.0` printed `Release v0.177.0 already exists, skipping` even though `gh release view v0.177.0` returned not found.\n- The `0.177.0` changelog section was 224,856 bytes, past the observed safe range for this repository's GitHub release body.\n- The desktop `workflow_run` fallback selected the stale latest release (`v0.153.0`) instead of the release tag attached to the completed CI run SHA.\n- Desktop packaging passed `--config package.json`, which made electron-builder treat the whole app manifest as a dedicated config object and reject the top-level `build` key.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Parse GitHub validation errors precisely and only skip exact duplicate release responses (`resource=Release`, `code=already_exists`, `field=tag_name`).\n- Cap generated GitHub release bodies at 120,000 bytes and append a link to the tagged full `CHANGELOG.md`.\n- Resolve desktop `workflow_run` builds from `github.event.workflow_run.head_sha`, verify the matching GitHub release exists, and skip instead of rebuilding a stale latest release.\n- Remove `--config package.json` from desktop electron-builder invocations and add a smoke guard against reintroducing it.\n- Add regression coverage for release body truncation, exact duplicate-release handling, generic validation failures, desktop tag resolution, and desktop builder config usage.\n- Add the full issue case study and archived evidence: https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/blob/issue-390-77cb1ef33735/docs/case-studies/issue-390/README.md\n\n## Template Reports\n\n- Rust template exact false-positive issue: https://github.com/link-foundation/rust-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template/issues/63\n- JavaScript template release body cap issue: https://github.com/link-foundation/js-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template/issues/71\n- Python template release body cap issue: https://github.com/link-foundation/python-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template/issues/16\n- C# template release body cap issue: https://github.com/link-foundation/csharp-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template/issues/21\n\n## Verification\n\n- `cargo fmt --all -- --check`\n- `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features`\n- `cargo test --all-features --verbose` (`767 passed; 0 failed; 1 ignored`)\n- `cargo test --doc --verbose`\n- `npm run --prefix desktop smoke`\n- `rust-script scripts/check-file-size.rs` (passed with existing line-count warnings only)\n- `git diff --check`\n","commits":[{"authoredDate":"2026-06-04T15:56:30Z","authors":[{"email":"drakonard@gmail.com","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","login":"konard","name":"konard"}],"committedDate":"2026-06-04T15:56:30Z","messageBody":"Adding .gitkeep for PR creation (default mode).\nThis file will be removed when the task is complete.\n\nIssue: https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/390","messageHeadline":"Initial commit with task details","oid":"295af01aa7a59dc96aba785c484eea523ae4ad57"},{"authoredDate":"2026-06-04T16:26:01Z","authors":[{"email":"drakonard@gmail.com","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","login":"konard","name":"konard"}],"committedDate":"2026-06-04T16:26:01Z","messageBody":"","messageHeadline":"Fix GitHub release recovery","oid":"55ea3a52063ada576471d2c91e613984f8b89b8c"},{"authoredDate":"2026-06-04T16:37:12Z","authors":[{"email":"drakonard@gmail.com","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","login":"konard","name":"konard"}],"committedDate":"2026-06-04T16:37:12Z","messageBody":"This reverts commit 295af01aa7a59dc96aba785c484eea523ae4ad57.","messageHeadline":"Revert \"Initial commit with task details\"","oid":"f09e27d2baa19b2da579e2ea1543ab8f68bd8e15"}],"files":[{"path":".github/workflows